cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SI

This paper deals with the problem of discovering latent structures from observed variables, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The proposed approach involves using quartets and tensors to recover the latent tree structure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms for learning from data, which is the main focus of the paper.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This sub-category covers topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms and data structures, which is relevant to the proposed divide-and-conquer algorithm.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers topics related to the design and analysis of intelligent agents and systems, which is relevant to the problem of discovering latent structures.
- cs.IT (Information Theory): This sub-category covers topics related to the transmission, processing, and storage of information, which is relevant to the use of tensors and rank characterization in the proposed approach.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category covers topics related to the analysis and modeling of social and information networks, which is relevant to the real world stock dataset used in the experiments.
